Ensure that at least 102400 KB (100MB) size is allocated for Application, Security and Server EventViewer log files. To configure log file size,1. Click Start > Run and type eventvwr.msc.2. Expand Windows Logs > Right click on Application, choose the Properties and set theMaximum Log Size to any size = or > than 100MB.3. Right click on Security, choose the Properties and set the Maximum Log Size to any size = or > than 100MB.4. Right click on Server, choose the Properties and set the Maximum Log Size to any size = or > than 100MB.5. Right click on Application, choose the Properties and set the Overwrite events older then = 7 days or as per bank s policy.6. Right click on Security, choose the Properties and set the Overwrite events older then = 7 days or as per bank s policy.7. Right click on Server, choose the Properties and set the Overwrite events older then = 7 days or as per bank s policy.Note: - Overwrite events is same as Retain Event Logs.Ensure that the logs are stored on other drive or system path instead of default system path.Ensure that backup and retention period is set according to the bank's policy.
